{{Politics of Northern Cyprus}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Northern Cyprus]] on 5 May 1985.<ref name=DD>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=cy011985 Türkische Republik Nordzypern, 5. Mai 1985 : Verfassung] Direct Democracy {{de icon}}</ref> The [[Constitution of Northern Cyprus|new constitution]] put forward by the [[Assembly of the Republic (Northern Cyprus)|Assembly of the Republic]] removed the term limits on the [[President of Northern Cyprus|President]], increased the number of seats in the Assembly from 40 to 60, set details on citizenship, the [[Flag of Northern Cyprus|national flag]] and the [[İstiklâl Marşı|national anthem]], and provided for mandatory referendums on changes to the constitution.<ref name=DD/> It was approved by 70.18% of voters.<ref name=DD/>
